ition":0},"title":"Hadith on Manners: Companions shake each other&#8217;s hands","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 31, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Qatadah reported: I said to Anas, \u201cDid the companions of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, shake hands?\u201d Anas said, \u201cYes.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 6263 Grade:\u00a0Sahih\u00a0(authentic) according to Al-Bukhari \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0642\u064e\u062a\u064e\u0627\u062f\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064f\u0644\u0652\u062a\u064f \u0644\u0650\u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0633\u064d \u0623\u064e\u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e\u062a\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064f\u0635\u064e\u0627\u0641\u064e\u062d\u064e\u0629\u064f \u0641\u0650\u064a \u0623\u064e\u0635\u0652\u062d\u064e\u0627\u0628\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0651\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0646\u064e\u0639\u064e\u0645\u0652 6263 \u0635\u062d\u064a\u062d \u0627\u0644\u0628\u062e\u0627\u0631\u064a\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":5761,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/31\/reward-shaking-hands\/","url_meta":{"origin":32229,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Manners: Muslims rewarded for shaking hands","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 31, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Bara' ibn 'Azib reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cNo two Muslims meet each other and shake hands but that Allah forgives them before they part.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 2727 Grade: Sahih li ghayrihi (authentic due to external evidence) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0628\u064e\u0631\u064e\u0627\u0621\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32231,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/16\/fall-like-leaves-shaking-hands\/","url_meta":{"origin":32229,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Greetings: Sins expiated by shaking hands","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 16, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, when the Muslim shakes hands with his brother, both of their sins fall away like the falling of leaves from a tree.\u201d Source: Musnad al-Bazza\u0304r 8335 Grade: Sahih li ghayrihi (authentic due to external evidence)\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19804,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/08\/28\/shaking-hands-expiate-sins\/","url_meta":{"origin":32229,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Greetings: Shaking hands erases sins","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 28, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Hudhayfah ibn al-Yaman reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \"Verily, when the believer meets another believer, greets him with peace, and shakes his hand, the sins of them both will shed like leaves falling from a tree.\" Source: al-Mu\u02bbjam al-Awsat\u0323 lil-T\u0323abara\u0304ni\u0304 245 Grade: Sahih\u00a0(authentic) according to\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":17061,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/11\/30\/greetings-shake-hands\/","url_meta":{"origin":32229,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Greetings: Best to shake hands, not bow or kiss","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 30, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: A man said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, when a man among us meets his brother or friend, should he bow for him?\u201d The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cNo.\u201d The man said, \u201cShould he embrace him and kiss him?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cNo.\u201d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":36093,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/05\/11\/companions-taqabbal-allah\/","url_meta":{"origin":32229,"position":5},"title":"Sahaba on Eid: May Allah accept from us and you","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 11, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Jubayr ibn Nufayr reported: The Companions of the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, when they met each other on the day of Eid, they would say to each other, \u201cMay Allah accept good deeds from us and from you.\u201d Source: S\u0323ala\u0304t al-'\u012adayn lil-Mah\u0323a\u0304mili\u0304 2\/218 Grade: Hasan\u2026","rel":"","con